role: The role involves leveraging advanced algorithms to improve Coupang’s customer experience by ensuring ultra-fast deliveries are on time. The candidate will drive the direction of technology across multiple teams and use statistical and machine learning techniques to bring value to customers.
description: The Applied Scientist will work within the Global Operation Tech (GOT) organization, responsible for systems that enable Coupang to deliver to customers within hours of orders being placed. Responsibilities include performing quantitative, economic, and numerical analysis of large-scale systems, applying theories of mathematical optimization, and collaborating effectively in cross-functional teams. Candidates should have a Master's degree in a quantitative discipline and 10+ years of experience in operations research and logistics. Preferred qualifications include a PhD and hands-on experience in supply chain optimization.

job_title: Blue Team DART – Staff Security Analyst
role: As a part of the Cyber Security Incident Response Team (CSIRT) in Seattle, you will analyze, respond to, and neutralize cyber threats while collaborating with relevant teams. You will develop detective capabilities and respond to credible threats to Coupang systems.
description: The BlueTeam is responsible for detecting and responding to credible threats. As a Senior Security Engineer, you will analyze and respond to security anomalies, conduct root cause analysis, and improve incident response policies. You must have a Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science or a related field and at least 4 years of experience in information security, with a preference for candidates with 12+ years of experience. Skills in threat hunting, security event analysis, and automation scripting are essential.

role: We are looking for a dynamic, motivated communications professional to join our growing Global Government Affairs team. This role is ideal for someone with 10 to 15 years of experience in the public policy space, ready to support a fast-paced global public affairs team.
description: Support development and execution of PR and communications strategies that build Coupang’s reputation and visibility with policymakers, stakeholders, and media. Assist in creating written communications, including press releases, media statements, briefing documents, Q&As, talking points, and newsletters, and blog posts. Monitor media, social channels, and policy news for stories relevant to Coupang; provide regular updates and media coverage reports. Help plan and execute events, briefings, and stakeholder engagements. Maintain media lists, stakeholder databases, and track outreach activities. Assist with coordination of external consultants, agencies, and vendors. Provide logistical and administrative support for the communications team to ensure projects run smoothly. Contribute creative ideas for campaigns, storytelling, and ways to strengthen Coupang’s reputation. Basic Qualifications: 10-15 years of experience in communications, public relations, public affairs, or related field. Strong writing and editing skills with the ability to tailor messages to different audiences. Experience with media relations and an interest in working with journalists. Prior experience supporting strategic multi-faceted communications campaigns with measurable results. Experience with event planning and logistics. Ability to manage multiple tasks, meet deadlines, and adapt in a fast-moving environment. Strong organizational skills and attention to detail. A collaborative and proactive team player with a “roll up your sleeves” attitude. Preferred Qualifications: Experience working with global corporations and/or tech companies, experience with digital advertising, sponsored content, and SEO.

role: We are looking for a hands-on Director of Engineering with deep technical expertise and a passion for building secure, reliable, and scalable systems. This role combines technical architecture leadership with people and delivery management.
description: Drive the security, quality, and reliability of our core platforms and AI systems while mentoring engineers, scaling engineering excellence, and partnering closely with product and leadership on strategic roadmaps. Build and grow a high-performing team of senior/staff-level engineers across geographies, fostering autonomy, trust, and accountability. Design and lead the architecture of secure, scalable backend systems using Java (Spring Boot) and AWS cloud-native services. Integrate Generative AI capabilities into product workflows responsibly and securely. Define API security patterns and API authorization at scale for microservices and service mesh environments. Lead design and implementation of authentication, authorization, and identity management solutions. Champion cryptography and PKI systems, secure SDLC practices, and compliance frameworks. Partner with leadership to deliver security-driven engineering roadmaps aligned with business priorities. Basic Qualifications: Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related technical field, 8+ years in software development and security engineering, proven experience designing and developing large-scale distributed systems, expertise in Java, Spring Boot, and AWS architecture/services, strong knowledge of security architecture. Preferred Qualifications: Recent hands-on experience building secure, distributed systems at scale, experience with cloud platforms for identity and ML infrastructure, familiarity with Generative AI integration, exposure to data security principles, ability to influence technical direction and mentor engineers.

role: The Coupang Media Group (CMG) is the advertising platform team focused on delivering advertising solutions. This senior individual contributor role involves creating and improving ad experiences across Coupang's apps and websites.
description: Product ownership for CMG Ads. Define the product vision, strategy, and roadmap to re-imagine our ads experience to deliver unique customer experiences while directing day-to-day execution towards the vision. Launch and improve ad products that surface highly relevant results for consumers and better conversion for advertisers. Work closely with business, engineering, internal/external partners, and customers to define project requirements and success criteria. Effectively communicate, collaborate and drive alignment with a variety of stakeholders including senior executives to ensure highly scalable and performance end-to-end experience for advertisers and shoppers. Basic Qualifications: Bachelor's Degree or equivalent experience, 8+ years of product management experience in advertising, proven ability to deliver in a complex environment, hands-on experience in an Agile environment, multiple successful launches of V1 products, excellent communication skills, ability to understand technical challenges. Preferred Qualifications: e-commerce experience, Master’s degree or MBA preferred, experience in international environments.

role: As the Director of Product Management for High Performance Compute (HPC), you will own the strategy, roadmap, and execution of our compute product line that powers advanced AI and data workloads. This role requires a strong mix of technical depth, customer empathy, and executional leadership.
description: You will define the product vision and roadmap for our cloud platform, including GPU-accelerated compute and specialized configurations for training and inference workloads. Responsibilities include identifying compute requirements, working cross-functionally with various teams, evaluating emerging technologies, ensuring operational excellence, and driving customer engagement. Basic qualifications include 8+ years of product management experience, experience with high-scale cloud compute services, and a Bachelor's degree in a related field. Preferred qualifications include familiarity with AI/ML frameworks and knowledge of GPU design trends.

role: Performs various duties related to FC Operations, including but not limited to Inbound, Inventory, Replenishment, Outbound, and Maintenance departments. Associates will be cross-trained before being assigned to a designated area.
description: Operate an RF gun/PDA device, breakdown, receive, and inspect inbound items, keep record of inventory, reconcile any discrepancies, and consolidate products, move items and carts from one location to another, pick, pack, stack, and ship items, promptly communicate any issues or damages to the Problem Solver, maintain safety and housekeeping standards in the department, may participate in training new associates. For Maintenance, remove trash, spills, and dropped/broken items, conduct routine inspections of the site and various equipment, handle basic repairs and oversee contractors when professional repairs are necessary. Basic qualifications include effective communication, ability to reach and write, basic math, computer literacy, ability to work independently or as part of a team, learning aptitude, detail-oriented, and ability to work in a fast-paced environment around machinery. Physical demands include remaining in a stationary position for 10+ hours, moving and walking for 10+ hours, bending and lifting up to 50 lbs, and pushing/pulling up to 50 lbs of exerted force. Preferred education and experience is a high school diploma or GED and similar FC experience.

role: The Forklift Driver operates industrial machinery and transports items within the fulfillment center. The role involves performing daily maintenance, following safety protocols, and organizing products.
description: As a Forklift Driver, you will perform daily forklift maintenance safety inspections, operate forklifts, balers, scrubbers, and pallet trucks, transport products, sort and organize items, and maintain safety standards. Basic qualifications include effective communication, basic math skills, computer literacy, and the ability to work in a fast-paced environment. Preferred education includes a high school diploma or GED, along with forklift experience and certifications.

role: The role involves reconciling discrepancies in inventory and performing miscellaneous job-related duties such as data entry and physical location checks. It requires effective communication and teamwork in a fast-paced environment.
description: Responsibilities include conducting cycle counts to account for all items in a location, removing expired products from inventory, auditing put aways for discrepancies, making necessary adjustments, and consolidating products using a PDA. Basic qualifications include effective communication, computer literacy, teamwork, learning aptitude, attention to detail, and the ability to work in a fast-paced environment. Physical demands include standing for over 10 hours, bending and lifting up to 60 lbs, and pushing/pulling up to 50 lbs. Preferred education is a high school diploma or GED with similar FC/Inventory Control experience.

role: The Operations Lead will perform various duties within the assigned department to facilitate operations safely at the Riverside Fulfillment Center. This includes providing safety leadership, training new hires, and engaging with team members to ensure a safe and efficient work environment.
description: The Operations Lead will provide training for new hires and existing workers on various topics including safety, quality, operations, and maintenance. Responsibilities include overseeing FC workers, ensuring all required trainings are completed, developing solutions to issues, maintaining safety and housekeeping standards, overseeing operational processes, assigning tasks, training and coaching warehouse team, and enforcing company policies and safety procedures. Preferred qualifications include a high school diploma or GED, one year+ experience in leading and training, and some experience in a warehouse environment.
